I was sad to hear about @thedavidcrosby passing away this evening. I met David at Sundance in 2019, but grew up with his music. I remember being so excited to meet him and couldn’t wait to tell my dad (for coolest son points). David loved his lattés. A caricature as he was, and then I sat on the floor and made the poster for the documentary he was promoting. He was really kind and gracious, and truly was blown away. Not just by the latté, but the character and emotion he recognized in my art and he made sure to tell me so. He told me to “Start painting, immediately”. Rest well #davidcrosby

DAD - by Chelsea Peretti @chelsanity feat. Will Schwartz @willschwartz100s 
I was asked to create latté art for this songs music video, and was so excited about this opportunity. This is what I was working on and the day the 2020 pandemic was announced, and we went into lockdown… I fell off the project and into the abyss. I was never able to share this but wanted to share today. The song does not reflect my experience with my father, but just reminds me that everyone has a unique experience and relationship with their parents and parent figures. I worked on this with my brothers, and this is the version edited by my brother @draandnoel . I’ll post a link to the music vid on Chelsea’s YouTube page in my story #fathersday #baristabrian #chelseaperetti #dad #daddy #latteart
Special thanks to @kooolkojak and @laurenxgold

好萊塢名人最愛「明星臉」Latte
把劇照神韻畫進咖啡拉花中
談到咖啡「拉花」，你可能看過一杂雲、愛心、落葉及卡通圝案等等，不過應該沒有看過把客人的臉放到拉花裡的
加拿大知名咖啡師布萊恩 (Brain Leonard)可是把「拉花」視為每杯咖啡的靈魂！把拿鐵上的濃郁奶泡當作專屬的彩
續畫布，捕捉點單容人的臉部神韻，細膩地把粉絲畫像
「拉花」進每一杯咖啡裡，這種容製化的拿鐵咖啡點子，為他赢來許多粉絲前往朝聖！
其中不泛好萊塢明星，像暢銷電影《哈利波特》男主角丹尼爾-雷德克里夫 (Daniel Raccliffe)、《穿著Prada的惡魔》時尚女魔頭梅莉-史翠普(Meryl Streep)《來去美國》喜劇演員艾迪•墨菲(Eddie Murphy)、
•漫威電影系列
《奇異博士》 男主角班奈狄克-康柏拜區 (Benedict
Cumberbatch)、及最近剛發表新電影作品《拿破崙》的男主角瓦昆-菲尼克斯(Joaquin Phoenix)其話題性十足的電影《小丑》 也在布萊恩的拉花下栩栩如生呈現！當然，除了名人劇照外，法國巴黎羅浮宮《蒙娜麗莎》也被放到咖啡拉花裡，畫風精巧讓小編都起立致敬惹！

I started my @mrcoffee Strawberry Fields Frappe at the (you guessed it) strawberry field! I’ve been visiting this local u-pick since I was a kid, and look forward to those fresh, sweet strawberries picked by my own hand every year. 
I made a syrup by boiling 1 cup of water and 1 cup of sugar (equal parts) and 1 cup of chopped strawberries. Mush the berries and let simmer and cool, then strain and tada! Delicious homemade syrup for coffee, ice cream, berries you name it. 
I love the Mr Coffee Frappe Maker machine because it is so adaptable to your preferences - the possibilities are endless. 
Here’s how I made the Strawberry Fields Frappe: 
Ice 
3 (Freshly picked) strawberries or try frozen for extra chill on hot days. 
Milk of your choice, maybe a scoop of vanilla ice cream! 
Syrup - I like to line my Mr. Coffee Iced tumbler first with the syrup and let that mix with my iced espresso, use however you like! 
I used an Espresso Roast for my concentrated coffee shot, which gives the Strawberry Fields Frappe a rich and bold coffee taste. The Mr Coffee Frappe Maker will brew this in minutes while you blend your frappe ingredients in the built-in blender 
Top with whipped cream! Berries and cream, need I say more? 🍓☕️✨

Painting a stranger in a latté ☺️☕️❤️

#baristabrian #latteart #coffee #barista

The first tastes of autumn have arrived in the form of a bright red, fresh off the branch apple. With the @mrcoffee latte maker, I’m bringing those crisp, sweet, warm and rosy notes to my morning latte. This machine makes it so easy to brew your favourite roast, hot or iced, in minutes. The milk frother works effortlessly to create beautiful, rich foam, however you like it! Hot or Cold foam, the 4-in-1 functionality of this machine makes sure everyone at home is happy with their cup :) 
 
My Apple Crisp Latte is made with a homemade syrup that literally took me minutes to make. Chop an apple into thin slices, then add to a pot with 1 cup of water, 1/4 cup of brown sugar, and two cinnamon sticks. Bring that to a boil, then strain into a mason jar and voila. Your kitchen is going to smell amazing, like there’s an apple crisp baking in the oven. I add 2-4 spoonfuls into my coffee, before adding the milk. It’s sweet but not too sweet, and the brown sugar really sets a nice warm tone. 
 
To paint the apple on top, I used a bit of red and green food dye. Just paint a red circle and add a little green stem and impress your guests with your incredible latte art!
